<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Resolving constraint violations when height is greater than max-height</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#min-max-widths" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Resolved width is max(max-height * width/height,min-width) and resolved height is max-height) when height is greater than max-height." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                width: 1in;
                height: 2in;
                max-height: 1in;
                background-color: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if a green square is visible.</p>
        <div></div>
    </body>
</html>